cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with 3D shape modeling using a neural network architecture. The use of auto-encoder-based pipeline and 3D spatial transformer network suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel factorized shape embedding space, which involves sub-space factorization, indicating that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of a neural network, suggesting that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
